$ DOM example: createElement

The following example uses `document.createElement('div')` to dynamically create a
→ development/web/HTML/tags/div[`<div>` HTML tag] and then appends it to
the HTML document's → development/web/HTML/tags/body[<body>] with `appendChild()`.

It additionally → development/web/CSS/javascript[changes the background style] of the created element to red so that the created element stands out more
distinctively.

